258
00:24:13,318 --> 00:24:15,843
with ulcers as bad
as any middle-aged businessman.

259
00:24:15,954 --> 00:24:17,979
Okay, I get the picture.

260
00:24:19,458 --> 00:24:22,188
- Now can I take her home?
- I think that's fine.

261
00:24:22,427 --> 00:24:23,587
No problem.

262
00:25:06,238 --> 00:25:08,035
You're sure you don't want a story?

263
00:25:08,940 --> 00:25:10,965
You don't have to read, you know.

264
00:25:11,443 --> 00:25:13,172
I can make one up for you.

265
00:25:16,481 --> 00:25:18,813
Do you want to tell me a story...

266
00:25:19,184 --> 00:25:21,516
about what happened today at Grandma's?

267
00:25:28,260 --> 00:25:29,818
You go to sleep, honey.

268
00:25:31,396 --> 00:25:33,296
I'll leave the hall light on.

269
00:25:46,378 --> 00:25:47,345
Damn.

270
00:25:51,049 --> 00:25:54,143
No outside calls. You're in isolation.
You know that.

271
00:25:54,252 --> 00:25:56,982
I tried to reach Dr. Raglan. He hasn't come.

272
00:25:57,088 --> 00:25:58,487
He's on his way.

273
00:26:00,292 --> 00:26:01,259
Chris...

274
00:26:04,529 --> 00:26:06,793
Is something wrong? Anything?

275
00:26:09,100 --> 00:26:11,034
Then it's me again.

276
00:26:13,438 --> 00:26:15,565
Nothing's wrong, except with me.

277
00:26:16,341 --> 00:26:20,209
No, that's Frank talking,
Frank twisting my words.

278
00:26:21,880 --> 00:26:25,839
He won't be patient, he won't trust me,
he won't wait until I get well.

279
00:26:27,352 --> 00:26:28,614
He thinks...

280
00:26:29,955 --> 00:26:31,752
that I'm turning into my mother.

281
00:26:31,856 --> 00:26:34,950
Day by day, moment by moment,
he thinks that I'm trying...

282
00:26:35,126 --> 00:26:37,651
to make Candy into Baby Nola.

283
00:26:38,029 --> 00:26:39,291
Is he right?

284
00:26:41,866 --> 00:26:45,358
No. That's the last thing on earth I'd...

285
00:26:52,277 --> 00:26:53,369
Who's that?

286
00:26:59,551 --> 00:27:00,643
It's Daddy.

287
00:27:02,687 --> 00:27:05,850
Frank hates me, Daddy. He despises me.

288
00:27:07,926 --> 00:27:10,190
He thinks I'm trying to harm my little girl...

289
00:27:10,295 --> 00:27:13,389
and I know that he's thinking of a way
to take her away.

290
00:27:14,165 --> 00:27:17,293
And that's very unfair of him.
That's very arrogant of him.

291
00:27:17,402 --> 00:27:20,098
You mustn't be too hard on him,
Nola, sweetheart.

292
00:27:20,305 --> 00:27:23,069
He's just trying to be a good,
protective father.

293
00:27:24,376 --> 00:27:25,400
No.

294
00:27:25,877 --> 00:27:26,935
Yes.

295
00:27:27,345 --> 00:27:30,143
He's just doing
what a good father should do.

296
00:27:30,382 --> 00:27:32,350
He's protecting his little girl.

297
00:27:33,018 --> 00:27:36,681
There's nothing wrong with that, is there?
He doesn't want to see her hurt.

298
00:27:36,788 --> 00:27:40,280
He doesn't want to see her hurt by anybody,
not even her own mother.

299
00:27:40,392 --> 00:27:43,293
Now, is there anything wrong with that?

300
00:27:45,430 --> 00:27:46,397
No.

301
00:27:48,333 --> 00:27:50,096
No, there isn't.

302
00:27:54,239 --> 00:27:57,072
After all, it's just what I did for you, isn't it?

303
00:27:59,344 --> 00:28:03,007
Frank's protecting Candy
the same way as I protected you, isn't he?

304
00:28:04,382 --> 00:28:05,349
Isn't he?

305
00:28:06,918 --> 00:28:07,885
No.

306
00:28:11,956 --> 00:28:13,514
What do you mean, "no"?

307
00:28:14,626 --> 00:28:17,151
- What do mean when you say "no"?
- I love you, Daddy.

308
00:28:20,532 --> 00:28:23,228
I don't want you to think
that I don't love you.

309
00:28:24,569 --> 00:28:26,161
I mean, you didn't.

310
00:28:27,939 --> 00:28:28,963
